Class AirportGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • cas2xb3_finalprototype.AirportGraph

  • public class AirportGraph
extends java.lang.Object
    The purpose of this class is to create a standard graph from airport edges that consist of AirportVertex objects with their own IDs. To it's core, it works the same way as a usual graph implementation from the Robert Sedgewick Algorithms 4 book, so the credit for that implementation goes to him.
    Author:
    Group 11 - Software Engineering 2XB3.
